    Class Description
    Alphabet
    The Alphabet class is used to convert letters to their numeric value (referred to as a letter's "index") and viceversa.
    Decryptor
    The Decryptor class is used to print the decrypted version of an encrypted file to the console.
    Encryptor
    The Encryptor class is the class entirely responsible for encrypting the text within a text document.
    KeyGenerator
    The KeyGenerator class is responsible for generating an encryption key (or "codex" as it is referred to within the program) text file containing a series of randomly generated numbers that meet parameters (such as complexity of randomly generated number or amount of randomly generated numbers) which are specified by the user.
    RunOneTimePadHardUI
    Class that handles and controls the console output and user inputs.
